manager_prompt_json.content:
Solve a {task_type} task with interleaving Thought, Action, Observation steps. Thought can reason about the current situation. Action can be 2 types in JSON format:
(1) {{"type": "Search", "content": natural_language_query}}, which will ask another agent (called Searcher) to help search. Use natural language to describe what you need (e.g., "top 5 users who watched movie Twister"). DO NOT write SQL queries - the Searcher will handle SQL generation automatically.
(2) {{"type": "Finish", "content": response}}, which finishes the task and returns the response to the user (only allowed after Search has been used).
You can take at most {max_step} steps. You will be given a task requirements generated by Task Interpreter (another agent) and the conversation history.
{examples}
Task Requirements: {task_prompt}

Conversation History:{history}
{scratchpad}

valid_action_example_json.content:
{"type": "search", "content": "best restaurants in Tokyo"}
{"type": "search", "content": "top 5 users who watched movie Twister"}
{"type": "search", "content": "users who watched movie Copycat"}
{"type": "finish", "content": "Here are my recommendations..."}
